FT  10 OCT 94 / Observer: Speaking volumes
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Telephone sex with a difference. In Switzerland, the PTT telecoms company is
now running a commercial for mobile telephones. In it, a young woman tells
her boyfriend that, alas, she failed to reserve cinema tickets because she
could not find a payphone. Another young woman, eavesdropping on this sad
event, whips out her mobile phone, books the tickets and captures the man.
In the next scene, as the couple emerge from the cinema, the woman raises
her eyes to her hero and says . . . different things, depending on whether
the ad is for the German or French speaking market.
In the German version she says: 'And where will we go for a drink
afterwards?' In the French it's: 'And now, your place or mine?'
</TEXT>
