FT  10 OCT 94 / Business Travel (Update): Japanese aftershock
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A strong undersea earthquake shook northern Japan yesterday, but there were
no reports of damage or injuries. It was thought to have been an aftershock
from the 8.2-magnitude quake last Tuesday, which killed at least 10 people
in the Russian-occupied Kuril Islands, just north of Japan, and caused 228
injuries in northern Japan from broken glass and falling objects.
Television reporters speaking from towns in Hokkaido said there were no
signs of damage.
