FT  08 OCT 94 / International Company News: Ameritech lifts job cuts total
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP-DJ
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Ameritech, the Chicago-based regional Bell telephone company, is to take a
Dollars 392m pre-tax charge in its third quarter to September 30 to cover
another 4,000 job losses, AP-DJ reports. The company said its forecast of
6,000 job cuts by 1995 had been revised to 10,000.
It said that net of one-off gains and after tax, the charge would be Dollars
168m. Last year's third - quarter earnings were Dollars 425m after a
one-time gain of Dollars 62m.
