</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Roy Wharton, the former chairman of Castlegate Securities, a
Reading-based loan management company, was yesterday sentenced to five
years' imprisonment for fraudulently mishandling Pounds 35m of investors'
funds.
He was convicted last month at Oxford Crown Court of two charges of
fraudulent trading. Having given assurances about the security of
investments, Mr Wharton pursued a speculative strategy which meant investors
bore most of the risk while he reaped the financial benefits.
