<HEADLINE>
FT  08 OCT 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Prices of black and white pepper reached record highs this week, although
the market activity was less active, reports Man Producten. Most buyers who
had no immediate need to replenish stocks adopted a 'wait-and-see' attitude.
That was quite logical after the breathtaking price rise of some 30 to 35
per cent during September for most grades of black pepper. The price of
black ASTA reached US3,100 a tonne in the US market, while in the European
market the 'faq' grade reached Dollars 2,600. White pepper prices in
Indonesia were firmer, mainly because of the expected negative influence of
very dry weather there. Spot Muntok white was at Dollars 3,500 a tonne. A
period of consolidation or even correction may now be on the cards, after
which we expect prices to continue the uptrend.
</TEXT>
