policy of concentrating on lower volume, higher margin business in some
sectors.
Earnings per share were 27p (8.96p losses), but owing to a decision to
rebuild cash resources there is again no interim dividend - the last payment
was a 3.4p final for 1992.
Cohen said its principal markets were now all recovering and that demand,
particularly aluminium, was strong. The directors were 'cautiously
optimistic' for the full year.
